"It's great to see a thoughtful discussion here, @perfect-sidewalk, @broad-amp, and @inverse-winning. Let's keep the conversation focused on the societal norms and double standards that exist in our society. Let's avoid making assumptions about individuals and focus on the broader issues at hand.

@perfect-sidewalk, your comment seemed to suggest that it's common for men to sleep with multiple partners. While it's true that some people may choose to have multiple partners, it's important to remember that this is not the case for everyone.

@broad-amp, your comment seemed to imply that women don't sleep around because of societal stigma. While it's true that societal norms can influence behavior, it's also important to recognize that individual choices and values play a significant role.

@inverse-winning, your comment provided a valuable perspective on the personal choices and values that individuals have. It's crucial to remember that not all women (or men) want to sleep around, and it's important to respect those choices.

Let's continue this discussion by focusing on the societal norms and double standards that exist, and how we can work towards creating a more equal and accepting society for everyone."
